With Freya's ability to freeze any enemy, the young Ice Queen has spent decades in a remote wintry palace raising a legion of deadly Huntsmen ‚Äì including Eric and warrior Sara ‚Äì only to find that her prized two defied her one demand: forever harden your hearts to love.  When Freya learns of her sister's demise, she summons her remaining soldiers to bring the Magic Mirror home to the only sorceress left who can harness its power. But once she resurrects Ravenna from the Mirror's golden depths, the wicked sister threaten this enchanted land with twice the darkness it's ever seen. text: I'm excited for this movie. As far as plot holes and originality goes, nothing is ever truly original, especially now that so many stories have been told and retold. Plot holes are also bound to exist, but since this is just a trailer, I think they will be filled by the actual movie.  *Also, this is NOT Frozen. Frozen was about the love between two sisters. Elsa was the only one with powers and she did not have a baby and a murderous, psycho sister. The only similarities are ice powers and having a sister. That's it. The rest of the story is completely different. Also, why are people expecting them to follow word for word the story of the Snow Queen? Just because there are ice powers involved does not mean they are the same character. If they were, I think they would have named her the Snow Queen and not the Ice Queen.

text: Why on earth does the voiceover twice emphasise on this one showing the story before Snow White when everything ( synopsis etc) indicates otherwise????  what kind of mockery towards the audience is this?? i mean, by releasing this second trailer and by having the voiceover say that, they almost had me convinced that it would be a prequel but after a very small research, i came to find out that the movie will be both a prequel/sequel. i really want to see how they have managed to explain all the inaccuracies that naturally occur between this one and the first film, such as: 1. how come Sara is still alive when it was clearly established she was dead, 2. how come Snow White's nane is not even mentionned after Ravenna's resurrection since she was the one who defeated her and became queen in the first place, i mean such a war takes place and yet we have no word of the queen?? how ridiculous is that?! and last but not least, 3. it is clear now that Eric will end up with  Sara, which means that they will have to explain how come his feelings for Snow, which actually brought her back from the sleep and were also the biggest twist in the tale (Snow didn't wake up by her prince) and, at least to me, created one of the most special and innovative parts of the movie, no longer exist? Eric was supposed to be in love with Snow now, so i guess that just because his wife turned out to be alive, he decided to give up on those feelings for Snow and go back to Sara. how incredibly inaccurate!! i strongly believe that this movie destroys everything the first movie was about, just because Kristen and Rupert did what they did.. such a waste..

text: MOVIE REVIEW and there's a VIDEO REVIEW on my channel (My own opinion so don't read it if you don't care): If I had to call this movie one thing it would be awful. This movie is about the snow queen who's child dies so she wants to rid the world of love. That is by far the dumbest villain motivation I have heard in awhile. It doesn't even make any sense. The fact that this movie even got made doesn't even make any sense to me. The plot line is thin with nothing new. The characters are one dimensional and the romance they have with one another especially Chris Hemsworth and his love interest is a joke in the film. This movie also can't decide if it wants to be a prequel, sequel, or a reboot which is laughable at times. The ending has a plot twist which I won't spoil but it was the most predictable plot twist that I've probably seen from a movie in a couple of years. This movie is as bad as it gets and isn't even enjoyable to watch. I have seen almost every movie this year and even I enjoyed God's of Egypt more then this. At least I could laugh in that movie from how bad it was. Don't see this cause you'd be wasting your time with this movie. This movie has no redeeming qualities so I won't even try to look for one. Fuck this movie and Fuck that hollywood thinks they can make this cash grab of a movie because they think their audience is going to support this. I know people have opinions and I respect that but I haven't met a single person that has liked this movie so far.

text: In my opinion the trailers were better than the movie itself. Spoiler alert:         I feel that the film didn't know if it wanted to be light or dark. I feel that in the same vein of the first film, it should have maintained the the same dark theme and tone throughout. I also think that they focused too much on the visuals. Sure, visuals are good, but I feel that the story should be first and foremost in terms of the amount of attention received. The trailers make me think that the two sisters are going to combine their armies and attempt to take over the world. I also dislike how they completely wrote off Ravenna's brother. In my opinion, that was just plain laziness. And it wouldn't have even been that bad if they didn't contradict the fact that the brother admitted to Eric's wife, Sarah. In the film, they just rewrote all of that. It was like they didn't think it would effect the film as a whole. However, I find that plot holes really detract from the experience. What were you guys' thoughts about the film?
